---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Personal Training / Karate Exercise"
  description="Personal training and karate exercise sessions at the Seishinkai Headquarters Dojo. Individual lessons (including iaido and self-defense lessons) scheduled to fit your own schedule, designed to help with dieting and metabolic syndrome."
  lang="en"
  path="/en/dojo/exe/"
>
  <section class="dojo-list">
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="section__title-area">
        <span class="section-label">PERSONAL TRAINING</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">
          Personal Training Karate Exercise
        </h1>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-page__lead">
        Individual lessons (including iaido and self-defense lessons)<br />
        [Seishinkai karate is a full-body conditioning exercise that avoids placing excessive strain on any one part of the body]<br />
        Seishinkai karate is not a competitive sport karate (modern karate), so it centers on the basics and kata.<br />
        It is an ideal conditioning exercise for middle-aged people looking to combat metabolic syndrome and for women who want to lose weight.<br />
        One member actually lost 20kg in a year. You can diet in a healthy way without straining your body.<br />
        We can also accommodate working people individually, so you can maintain a steady practice routine.<br />
        If you haven't had success at a sports club or with dietary therapy, please come and try this out.<br />
        Sessions are held by individual appointment (reservation required) outside of the headquarters dojo's regular practice days. As with regular classes, you can also earn kyu/dan rank.
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">Personal Training Fees (Base Rates)</h2>
      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/dojo/exe/img8.jpg"
            alt="Personal training fee schedule"
            class="u-object-contain"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p class="detail-page__note">
        Since various equipment is used during karate conditioning exercises, you will first need to purchase hand and foot supporters.<br
        />
        ※Personal training members may also take part in the headquarters' regular classes or branch classes (¥2,000/session). Note that if a regular member receives individual instruction, the fee above is halved.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong
          >※The base hours for personal training are during times when there is no headquarters practice: Mon/Tue/Wed/Thu/Fri/Sat 14:00-15:00, Sun 15:00-16:30<br
          />
          An additional fee of ¥1,000 is required for weekday evenings (after 20:00) and Sundays.</strong
        >
      </p>

      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/photo/4.jpg"
            alt="A scene from an individual lesson"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/photo/3.jpg"
            alt="A scene from an individual lesson"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/photo/5.jpg"
            alt="A scene from an individual lesson"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">Diet & Health Class</h2>
      <p>
        ◆Hours: Available from 13:30 to 23:00<br />
        ◆Session length: 45–90 minutes (per session)<br />
        ※Days of the week etc. are arranged individually
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">Venue: Seishinkan Headquarters Dojo</h2>
      <div class="detail-gallery">
        <figure>
          <img
            src="/assets/images/legacy/base/sakaedori.jpg"
            alt="Seishinkan Headquarters Dojo (Sakaedori)"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>There is a parking lot at the rear of the building</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/〒003-0021+北海道札幌市白石区栄通２丁目１−２７/@43.0409785,141.3938016,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x5f0b2bb4690b9e5f:0x622b301003410409!8m2!3d43.0409785!4d141.3959903"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          >2-1-27 Sakaedori, Shiroishi-ku, Sapporo (along Tohoku-dori)</a
        >　About 10 min / 800m on foot from Shiroishi Subway Station
      </p>

      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">Fees</h2>
      <p>
        ■Enrollment fee ¥7,000<br />
        ■Annual registration fee ¥5,800 (insurance included)<br />
        ■Base monthly fee ¥1,500<br />
        ■Karate gi ¥10,000〜 (※practice gi rental is also available, may incur a fee)<br />
        ■Heating fee (Oct–Mar) ¥500/session, charged separately<br />
        ※If you would like to also join the regular class, you can switch over to it partway through
      </p>

      <p class="detail-page__back">
        <a href="/en/dojo/">← Back to the Dojo & Class List</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
